---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="What Files Should I Ask For? | Logo Brief Guide"
  description="Know what logo files and deliverables to ask for so you do not end up with a pretty image that is useless later."
  pathname="/what-files-should-i-ask-for/"
>
  <section class="prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Supporting page</p>
    <h1>What files should I ask for?</h1>
    <p>
      One of the most common buyer mistakes is paying for a logo and receiving
      only a flat image file. Ask for the right set of deliverables at the start.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section two-col">
    <div class="soft-card">
      <h2>Core files to request</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Vector/source file</li>
        <li>PNG with transparent background</li>
        <li>JPG or PNG for simple use</li>
        <li>Black version</li>
        <li>White or reversed version</li>
        <li>Horizontal and stacked variations if relevant</li>
        <li>Favicon or social-icon crop if needed</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="soft-card">
      <h2>Why this matters</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Vectors scale cleanly</li>
        <li>Transparent files work on many backgrounds</li>
        <li>Color variations prevent future headaches</li>
        <li>Alternate lockups help with layout needs</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Simple rule</h2>
      <p>
        If a designer cannot clearly explain what files you will receive, do not
        assume you are getting everything you need.
      </p>
      <p><a class="button" href="/logo-designer-red-flags/">See the red flags</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
